definitions: Of great or more than average height, especially with reference to a position above the ground or above the average level.
Extending a long way upwards; tall.
Greater than the usual level or amount.
Of a high degree or standard.
Under the influence of drugs or alcohol.
Of a sound or note, having a high frequency or pitch.
Of a period or time, at its peak or most intense point.
examples: the high point of his career
